    "description": "A hypothetical road segment in the vicinity of forts at Djenndel and Henchir Mdila (ancient Midili?) in modern Algeria's Bir El Ater province.",
    "details": "<p>BAtlas and BAtlDir include this route \"Djenndel → Midili?\", with BAtlDir citing \"Baradez 1947\" (a work that does not appear in the directory's bibliography) without page numbers or further indicia. Perhaps Baradez 1949 was meant: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Baradez, J. <i>Fossatum Africae: Recherches Aériennes Sur l’organisation Des Confins Sahariens à l’époque Romaine</i>. Paris, 1949.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>Itiner-e</em> also includes this route (see \"References\"), citing \"Salama 1951\" without page numbers or further indicia. The work in question must be:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Salama, Pierre. <em>Les voies romaines de l'Afrique du Nord.</em> Impr. officielle, 1951.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>",
